"description": "<p>Oh my, it took me much longer than usual to compose this month's topic for discussion. I've tried to incorporate a number of topic suggestions from members, which had something of a common thread. As such, this month's topic deviates from our recent discussions regarding more metaphysical strains of philosophy in favor of more political strains. To get the discussion going, I've written a brief essay that references ideas from Plato, Aristotle and DeTocqueville regarding the evolution of stable and “right constitutions”. Click the ‘Files’ button on the left side of this page and there you will find the essay I uploaded on February 21st. I hope it inspires a lively discussion.</p> <p>As usual, we will meet at 7pm, settle in, meet and greet, and kick off the topic at 7:30pm.</p> <p>Cheers,<br/>Josh</p> ",
